Malawi to Boost Cotton Farmers as Tobacco Declines, Zodiak Says

-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 
2011-08-19T10:23:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/malawi-to-boost-cotton-farmers-as-tobacco-declines-zodiak-says.html
Malawi will seek to increase the
number of cotton growers in the country because of declining
revenue from tobacco, Zodiak Broadcasting Station reported,
citing Agriculture Minister Peter Mwanza.  The government wants to boost the number of cotton farmers
to 500,000 from about 100,000, the broadcaster cited Mwanza as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre at 
 fjomo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  